
[1]conjugal

   CONJUGAL, a. [L., marriage; to yoke or couple. See Join and Yoke.]

   1. Belonging to marriage; matrimonial; connubial; as conjugal relation;
   conjugal ties.

   2. Suitable to the married state; becoming a husband in relation to his
   consort, or a consort in relation to her husband; as conjugal
   affection.
